== Open-source dependencies ==

speculo is built using the following open-source packages, consumed as
standard npm dependencies (see packages/*/package.json for the full list).
No source code from these projects is embedded or modified in speculo:

- Stoplight Spectral (https://github.com/stoplightio/spectral) - Apache-2.0
  OpenAPI linting engine; used for spec validation in
  packages/api/src/services/specProcessor.ts.

- Scalar (https://github.com/scalar/scalar) - MIT
  API documentation rendering; used for the interactive docs UI at
  /docs/:service/:branch.

- Hono (https://github.com/honojs/hono) - MIT
  Web framework powering the API server.

- Drizzle ORM (https://github.com/drizzle-team/drizzle-orm) - Apache-2.0
  Database access layer for PostgreSQL.

- Model Context Protocol SDK (https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk) - MIT
  MCP server implementation for AI assistant integration.

- Swagger Parser (https://github.com/APIDevTools/swagger-parser) - MIT
  OpenAPI / Swagger 2.0 parsing.

- Radix UI (https://www.radix-ui.com) - MIT
  Accessible UI primitives in the web frontend.

- Tailwind CSS (https://tailwindcss.com) - MIT
  Utility-first CSS framework.

== Standards ==

- OpenAPI Specification (https://www.openapis.org) - Apache 2.0
  Used for the spec format speculo stores and serves.

- Model Context Protocol (https://modelcontextprotocol.io) - MIT
  Used for the AI assistant integration protocol.
